WEBVTT

00:02.070 --> 00:04.505
[ Upbeat music plays ]

00:04.538 --> 00:14.515
♪♪

00:14.548 --> 00:17.151
♪♪

00:26.794 --> 00:27.961
[ Dramatic flourish plays ]

00:27.995 --> 00:29.763
And in other news,
scientists have discovered

00:29.797 --> 00:30.898
a completely new color --

00:30.931 --> 00:33.467
a mixture of blue
and red called "bled."

00:33.501 --> 00:35.736
And here it is on TV
for the first time.

00:35.769 --> 00:37.538
Yeah, typical!

00:37.571 --> 00:39.440
Stuff always breaks just when
the warranty runs out.

00:39.473 --> 00:40.708
When did it run out?

00:40.741 --> 00:42.443
About 20 years ago.
Hmm.

00:42.476 --> 00:44.845
Uh, I think there's something
wrong with our mirror too.

00:44.878 --> 00:46.480
I don't think
that's the mirror.

00:46.514 --> 00:49.617
Yeah. You look like a pair
of English buttocks.

00:49.650 --> 00:52.120
Yeah, well, at least
I'm not eating kitty litter.

00:52.153 --> 00:52.553
Huh?

00:52.586 --> 00:54.155
Eww! Mom!

00:54.188 --> 00:55.723
Mom:
I got confused, okay?

00:55.756 --> 00:58.159
Everything was in black
and white at the supermarket.

00:58.192 --> 01:00.161
I chose that one because
I like the picture.

01:00.194 --> 01:02.596
It literally says
"non-clumping" on the box.

01:02.630 --> 01:05.433
Uh, I assumed that meant
it was full of fiber.

01:05.466 --> 01:07.201
Huh? Aah!

01:07.235 --> 01:10.338
Okay, something weird
is going on here.

01:10.371 --> 01:11.772
[ Horns honking ]

01:12.873 --> 01:15.109
What the what?

01:15.143 --> 01:16.310
[ Honking continues ]
[ Siren chirps ]

01:16.344 --> 01:18.512
All right, all right.
Everybody calm down.

01:18.546 --> 01:19.747
I'll take care of this.

01:19.780 --> 01:21.815
Okay, dark-gray car,
move forward.

01:21.849 --> 01:23.751
Aah! Not you!

01:23.784 --> 01:25.286
Light gray!
Reverse, reverse!

01:25.319 --> 01:26.587
Aah!

01:26.620 --> 01:28.189
Medium gray, move forward!

01:28.222 --> 01:29.190
Aah!

01:29.223 --> 01:31.225
Somebody do something!

01:32.760 --> 01:34.595
What is going on
around here?

01:34.628 --> 01:37.398
It's like the color's
been sucked out of the world.

01:37.431 --> 01:38.399
[ Cellphone chimes ]

01:38.432 --> 01:41.302
"Excited for our blind date
and first kiss.

01:41.335 --> 01:43.337
I'll be the one wearing gray."

01:43.371 --> 01:44.672
[ Gasps ] Huh?

01:46.740 --> 01:48.108
Eh.

01:51.545 --> 01:53.814
[ Grunting ]

01:53.847 --> 01:55.383
[ Crowd cheering ]
[ Whistle blows ]

01:56.817 --> 01:58.786
[ Cheering stops ]

01:58.819 --> 02:01.455
The spell is broken!

02:01.489 --> 02:04.392
I don't have to spend my life
supporting this team anymore.

02:04.425 --> 02:06.860
Now I can finally dedicate
my time to my real passion --

02:06.894 --> 02:08.629
close-up magic.

02:08.662 --> 02:11.399
And I can get back to
the greatest pastime of all --

02:11.432 --> 02:12.666
embroidery!

02:12.700 --> 02:14.635
Magic.
Embroidery.

02:14.668 --> 02:16.704
Magic!
Embroidery!

02:16.737 --> 02:19.273
[ Indistinct shouting ]

02:19.307 --> 02:19.940
Juicy!

02:19.973 --> 02:22.343
Hmm.
What's all this now?

02:22.376 --> 02:24.378
There's something
we're not seeing.

02:24.412 --> 02:28.148
[ Clang! ]
Oh! Dagnabbit.

02:30.251 --> 02:31.419
Oh!

02:31.452 --> 02:32.753
Aw, come on, man.

02:32.786 --> 02:34.188
No, no, no.
Watch out, dude.

02:34.222 --> 02:35.589
It's all right.
I got this.

02:35.623 --> 02:36.590
[ Clang! ]
Ow!

02:36.624 --> 02:38.826
Right in the...neck.

02:40.628 --> 02:41.962
Huh.
What's this?

02:41.995 --> 02:43.464
What is
going on here?

02:43.497 --> 02:45.666
This place looks like
a gas-station restroom

02:45.699 --> 02:46.900
under UV light.

02:46.934 --> 02:48.236
I know what happened.
Aah!
Aah!

02:48.269 --> 02:49.637
The kid who used
to clean off the tags

02:49.670 --> 02:51.272
hasn't come for a while.

02:51.305 --> 02:53.941
Uh, you got a -- you got
a little bit of paint on you.

02:53.974 --> 02:56.377
Ah.
Did I get it?

02:56.410 --> 02:57.978
Uh, yeah, sure.

02:58.011 --> 02:59.747
One last thing --
Could you point the way out?

02:59.780 --> 03:02.583
Sure,
it's that way.

03:02.616 --> 03:04.952
I really don't know why
I thought that would help.

03:09.990 --> 03:11.825
I think there might be
trouble ahead.

03:11.859 --> 03:13.761
Yeah.
I can smell it.

03:13.794 --> 03:14.995
[ Inhales sharply ]

03:15.028 --> 03:16.497
Well, it actually
smells like popcorn.

03:16.530 --> 03:19.800
[ Popping! ]
Aah! You can't stay here!

03:19.833 --> 03:21.335
What? Why?

03:21.369 --> 03:22.236
Aah! Aah!

03:22.270 --> 03:24.472
The sun! Aah!
The sun!

03:24.505 --> 03:26.340
What's wrong
with the sun?

03:26.374 --> 03:29.910
The nice boy who did
the recycling has given u--

03:29.943 --> 03:31.579
Wait, has what?

03:31.612 --> 03:34.815
[ Weakly ] He's given up.

03:34.848 --> 03:36.884
So what?
What the what, dude?!

03:36.917 --> 03:38.486
You look like
a trucker's elbow!

03:38.519 --> 03:40.654
You look like
a medieval coin sack!

03:40.688 --> 03:42.323
Wait a minute.

03:42.356 --> 03:44.325
They stopped recycling,
didn't they? [ Gasps ]

03:44.358 --> 03:46.860
And burned a hole
in the ozone layer!

03:46.894 --> 03:48.562
[ Stammering ]
Ah, I got it!

03:48.596 --> 03:50.831
Of course! The sewers!
Good idea!

03:50.864 --> 03:53.467
[ Splashes ]

03:53.501 --> 03:56.904
You meant use the cover
as a shade, didn't you?

03:56.937 --> 03:59.307
Yeah,
that's what you meant.

03:59.840 --> 04:01.342
[ Clang! ]
Hmm.

04:01.375 --> 04:03.544
What's going on here?
Stop!

04:03.577 --> 04:06.280
I'm sorry, kids,
but you can't go this way!
Why?

04:06.314 --> 04:07.881
The kid who used to feed
the ducks has stopped.

04:07.915 --> 04:09.350
Pbbt. So?

04:09.383 --> 04:10.250
So?

04:10.284 --> 04:11.819
[ Indistinct shouting
and screaming ]

04:11.852 --> 04:13.454
[ Birds cheeping ]

04:19.627 --> 04:22.029
Uh, I guess we'll go via
the old folks' home, then.

04:22.062 --> 04:23.764
I wouldn't.
Why?

04:23.797 --> 04:26.434
The kid who used to run
the bingo has stopped doing it.

04:26.467 --> 04:28.669
MAN: Mayday! Mayday!
We need backup!

04:28.702 --> 04:30.638
They're coming through
the gosh-darn walls!

04:30.671 --> 04:32.440
Aaah!

04:33.474 --> 04:34.442
Whoa.

04:34.475 --> 04:36.310
Turns out the rules of bingo
are the only rules

04:36.344 --> 04:37.845
in an old folks' home, huh?

04:37.878 --> 04:39.680
[ Explosion ]
Whoa!
All right, you know what?

04:39.713 --> 04:42.950
It's every man for himself now!
By the way, avoid the zoo!

04:42.983 --> 04:45.553
The kid who used to volunteer
there has given up too!

04:45.586 --> 04:46.720
[ Screeches ]

04:46.754 --> 04:48.456
[ Inhales sharply ]

04:48.489 --> 04:50.891
I think I'll take my chances
with the ducks.

04:53.861 --> 04:56.997
Dude, the atmosphere
is getting kind of creepy.

04:57.030 --> 04:59.032
Yeah.
It's like we're being hunted.

04:59.066 --> 05:02.336
[ Gasps ] Not hunted.
Scouted.

05:03.837 --> 05:04.838
[ Exhales slowly ]

05:08.742 --> 05:09.943
Clever boy.

05:09.977 --> 05:11.078
Scouts.

05:11.111 --> 05:12.846
Aah!

05:12.880 --> 05:15.549
[ Indistinct shouting ]

05:15.583 --> 05:16.650
You're scouts!

05:16.684 --> 05:18.386
Aren't you supposed to be nice,
build birdhouses,

05:18.419 --> 05:20.087
and play the bugle
and junk?

05:20.120 --> 05:23.757
Our scoutmaster left us, so
we're an army without a leader.

05:23.791 --> 05:25.593
This is our territory now.

05:25.626 --> 05:27.661
You're either with us
or against us.

05:27.695 --> 05:29.630
Aah! We're with you!
We're with you!

05:29.663 --> 05:31.499
Huh!
What's our motto, then?

05:31.532 --> 05:33.934
I'll give you a clue.
Starts with "B."

05:33.967 --> 05:38.105
"Be...lieve in men who wear
short shorts in the woods"?

05:38.138 --> 05:39.740
Badges!
Scouts love badges, right?

05:39.773 --> 05:41.709
You want badges?

05:41.742 --> 05:44.478
When the leader left,
we found his stash of badges.

05:44.512 --> 05:46.647
We have all the badges now.

05:46.680 --> 05:48.549
Wait, aren't you
supposed to earn them

05:48.582 --> 05:49.950
by actually
learning the skills?

05:49.983 --> 05:52.553
Pff.
Like, technically, yeah.

05:52.586 --> 05:54.755
So did you "technically"
learn how to tie knots?

05:54.788 --> 05:57.357
Uh...fshh.
Mm...

06:00.060 --> 06:02.062
Meh,
shame they didn't earn

06:02.095 --> 06:03.431
their self-defense badges
either.

06:03.464 --> 06:05.399
[ Thunder crashes ]

06:07.535 --> 06:10.103
Hmm. Looks like we found
the source of it all.

06:10.137 --> 06:11.539
Come on,
let's investi--

06:11.572 --> 06:14.508
Oh, what's the point,
Darwin?!

06:14.542 --> 06:18.746
We'll never figure out
what's going on!

06:18.779 --> 06:21.915
What am I talking about?
There's no reason we wouldn't.

06:21.949 --> 06:23.717
O-kay.

06:23.751 --> 06:24.652
No!

06:24.685 --> 06:27.455
Life just pointlessly
stirs up the dust

06:27.488 --> 06:30.591
that you'll
eventually turn into!

06:30.624 --> 06:32.660
[ Both sobbing ]

06:35.195 --> 06:38.098
Ah.
That makes sense. Alan.

06:38.131 --> 06:42.870
Someone like him gives up, then
the whole world loses its glow.

06:42.903 --> 06:45.806
Hey, Alan.
What's wrong?

06:45.839 --> 06:46.707
I've lost it.

06:46.740 --> 06:47.908
It's all right, man.

06:47.941 --> 06:50.911
Whatever it is, no one ever
thought you had it, anyway.

06:50.944 --> 06:52.946
Psht!
All right, fine.

06:52.980 --> 06:54.014
What have you lost,
Alan?

06:54.047 --> 06:56.750
My faith in the world.

06:56.784 --> 06:59.620
So that's why you stopped
all your voluntary work.

06:59.653 --> 07:01.855
But why?
You were doing great.

07:01.889 --> 07:06.527
No matter how much I try,
the world will never be perfect.

07:06.560 --> 07:07.861
Well, you got to get
back on the horse.

07:07.895 --> 07:09.830
Oh, why bother?

07:09.863 --> 07:12.199
Because we need people like you
to do all that work,

07:12.232 --> 07:14.067
so that people like me
don't have to.

07:14.101 --> 07:17.237
There's no point, Gumball.
People don't change.

07:17.270 --> 07:19.006
Goodness knows
I tried to stay positive

07:19.039 --> 07:20.708
and turn the other cheek.

07:20.741 --> 07:22.843
But what happens when you
run out of cheeks to turn?

07:22.876 --> 07:24.645
Well, I can think of
a couple more cheeks --

07:24.678 --> 07:27.481
But, Alan, you changed
the lives of so many people.

07:27.515 --> 07:28.949
Yeah,
but what about him?

07:28.982 --> 07:31.519
In spite of all the effort
I've made to be friends,

07:31.552 --> 07:33.621
he still
can't look me in the eye.

07:33.654 --> 07:36.990
Ha! That's not --
that's not true.

07:37.024 --> 07:38.559
Yes, Alan.

07:38.592 --> 07:40.894
We are frie--
[ Gags ]

07:40.928 --> 07:42.630
We are frie--
[ Gags ]

07:42.663 --> 07:44.865
See? He's physically
incapable of saying

07:44.898 --> 07:46.867
anything remotely positive
about me.

07:46.900 --> 07:48.869
Prove him wrong.
Give him a hug.

07:48.902 --> 07:52.205
Uh...eh...uh...

07:52.239 --> 07:54.942
There you go.
Good job.

07:54.975 --> 07:56.677
Give him a good squeeze.

07:56.710 --> 07:59.613
That's right.
Can you feel the love?

08:02.583 --> 08:05.185
Ah, no, no, no, no.
That's too much love.

08:05.218 --> 08:07.020
[ Gasping ]
See?!

08:07.054 --> 08:09.523
Well, I'm sorry, man, but that's
just not how life works, okay?

08:09.557 --> 08:11.992
Oh, really?
Then how does it work?

08:12.025 --> 08:13.260
[ Sighs ] Well, Alan,

08:13.293 --> 08:15.763
life doesn't work
in black and white.

08:15.796 --> 08:18.165
Let me give you
a little insight.

08:18.198 --> 08:23.604
♪ It's one big shade of gray

08:23.637 --> 08:26.306
And the dark kind,
I'm afraid to say.

08:26.339 --> 08:28.742
♪ Because there's war
and fighting ♪

08:28.776 --> 08:30.544
♪ And the bad guy often wins

08:30.578 --> 08:32.179
♪ So you have to find
some comfort ♪

08:32.212 --> 08:33.681
♪ in the smallest
little things ♪

08:33.714 --> 08:35.082
♪ There's shouting
and there's stealing ♪

08:35.115 --> 08:37.084
♪ There are mortgages to pay

08:37.117 --> 08:40.187
♪ But that's a grown-up thing,
and you are still a kid today ♪

08:40.220 --> 08:43.056
♪ The prospects for society
are turning for the worst ♪

08:43.090 --> 08:46.193
♪ The environment is suffering
and might not be reversed ♪

08:46.226 --> 08:49.563
♪ But at least the nasty kid
who makes every day so rough ♪

08:49.597 --> 08:50.898
♪ In the end gets hit by karma

08:50.931 --> 08:52.700
♪ Which will kind of
make you laugh ♪

08:52.733 --> 08:55.803
♪ And, sure, the future's
looking pretty grim ♪

08:55.836 --> 08:59.039
♪ The light on the horizon
is pretty dim ♪

08:59.072 --> 09:01.975
♪ But you're a kid and all of
life is still ahead of you ♪

09:02.009 --> 09:05.579
♪ Unlike the 90-something guy
who got the avian flu ♪

09:05.613 --> 09:08.716
♪ Life ain't perfect,
it's meh ♪

09:08.749 --> 09:11.785
♪ Some bits are okay,
but most of it is ugh ♪

09:11.819 --> 09:14.822
♪ Life ain't perfect,
it's meh ♪

09:14.855 --> 09:16.590
♪ You got to find the good

09:16.624 --> 09:17.625
♪ That's in this
great big load of... ♪

09:17.658 --> 09:18.959
Pbht!

09:18.992 --> 09:20.761
Gumball: ♪ And, yes, the more
you work on it ♪

09:20.794 --> 09:22.596
♪ The worse it seems to get

09:22.630 --> 09:24.031
Darwin:
♪ Looking at the news

09:24.064 --> 09:25.833
♪ Can make you break out
in a sweat ♪

09:25.866 --> 09:28.802
♪ That's the way life is
so you got to deal with it ♪

09:28.836 --> 09:30.671
♪ There's not much else
to say right now ♪

09:30.704 --> 09:32.305
♪ To lift your spirit

09:32.339 --> 09:34.141
[ Somber music plays ]

09:34.174 --> 09:35.976
♪ Tell me how's all that

09:36.009 --> 09:39.312
♪ Supposed to
make me feel better? ♪

09:39.346 --> 09:40.948
♪ My life's unraveling

09:40.981 --> 09:45.018
♪ Just like threads
pulled from a sweater ♪

09:45.052 --> 09:48.188
♪ There's no sunshine
in my future ♪

09:48.221 --> 09:50.724
♪ It is gray, desaturated

09:50.758 --> 09:56.797
♪ Tell me why
I shouldn't feel so deflated ♪

09:58.065 --> 09:58.966
Because...

09:58.999 --> 10:00.801
Because...

10:00.834 --> 10:03.737
♪ If you stop
halfway up the mountain ♪

10:03.771 --> 10:06.840
♪ You will never
see the view ♪

10:06.874 --> 10:08.976
♪ But when you look
how far you've climbed ♪

10:09.009 --> 10:12.713
♪ You'll find the courage
to pull through ♪

10:12.746 --> 10:14.114
♪ You'll wonder
how on earth ♪

10:14.147 --> 10:15.983
♪ You can put up
with all of this ♪

10:16.016 --> 10:20.788
♪ Then you'll come across
a memory of perfect bliss ♪

10:20.821 --> 10:23.156
♪ So keep following
the light ♪

10:23.190 --> 10:26.193
♪ No matter
how much your heart aches ♪

10:26.226 --> 10:27.895
♪ 'Cause this sad old world

10:27.928 --> 10:31.164
♪ Will need your hope to fix it
when it breaks ♪

10:31.198 --> 10:34.334
♪ And at times
when you can't take it ♪

10:34.367 --> 10:36.870
♪ And you want the day to end

10:36.904 --> 10:40.107
♪ Take my hand
and you will find ♪

10:40.140 --> 10:48.782
♪ Life is beautiful,
my friend ♪

10:48.816 --> 10:51.118
[ Birds chirping ]
[ Sighs ]

10:51.151 --> 10:52.352
Thank you, Gumball.

10:52.385 --> 10:53.320
I guess this
makes us friends now.

10:53.353 --> 10:55.989
What? Pff!
No.

10:56.023 --> 10:58.191
Oh.

10:58.225 --> 11:00.027
All right.
Maybe a little.

11:00.060 --> 11:01.795
Mm!

11:03.096 --> 11:13.006
♪♪

11:13.040 --> 11:22.750
♪♪

11:22.783 --> 11:32.292
♪♪
